    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A P0171 code is a lean condition, meaning your car is running with too much air in the fuel mixture. Since you've checked the MAF sensor and it's solid, you might want to look at the mass airflow sensor (MAF) again to ensure it's not dirty or faulty. Also, check the fuel injectors for proper function, as they could be clogged or leaking, causing an imbalance in the air-fuel mixture. Additionally, inspect the oxygen sensors; if they're not working correctly, they can send incorrect data to the engine control unit (ECU), leading to a lean condition. Lastly, consider checking the fuel pressure and the fuel pump itself, as these could also be contributing factors.",
